metadata.name: Skull Village  #45
metadata.description:
In this generative project, you will see a combination of digital art and modern art and fine art, as well as using elements produced through artificial intelligence.

This project is a digital collage and different layers are designed to make it
In this project, there are 14 different Traits, which are many layers under each.
There are a total of 122 different layers that are combined, which makes it less likely that two images are close to each other because only 256 NFTs are randomly minted out of 3,910,952,263,680 different states.
This project is the result of more than 100 hours of effort and therefore this project will be very valuable
In addition, due to the fact that some layers are more special, this project has a rarity


Designed by: @3d_punk
Made in 2022

metadata.name: Leviathan #14
metadata.description:
Leviathan is a generative collection of large bodies made form particles, materialised from the viewers own subconscious. Atoms form gargantuan objects - subatomic monoliths and microscopic giants. Playing with the sense of scale it draws on the viewer’s subjective way of associating forms, a pattern that becomes a mirror, a skeleton for them to project. 

Part artist, part viewer. Leviathan asks us to question these relationships of creation, ownership and meaning. It is a chemical reaction that the artist starts and you finish. A colossal dream we are all sharing together - a leviathan.


Controls:
s or double tap: Download image
1 : Download 2400 x 4000
2 : Download 3600 x 6000
3 : Download 4800 x 8000
4 : Download 7200 x 12000

metadata.name: VHX-1 #121
metadata.description:
• Interdimensional pixel portals •


I generated the raw base GAN seeds used in this piece offline from various custom styleGAN models. All the mixing and processing steps are done generatively online in p5.js by the VHX algorithm •


Controls:
[s] save as PNG.


Notes:
Artworks take a few seconds to render.

metadata.name: Obliques #180
metadata.description:
Obliques are a reinterpretation of Parallels, a collection of AI generated color fields by Marc Maurer. Many of the pieces in that collection are CC0, which basically means they can be reused for other projects, like this one.

Obliques takes artifacts from Parallels and uses them as brushes, painting slices of the original image on the canvas in a (hopefully) pleasant, chaotic way.

About 10% will be "Glitched".

The "Source Material" property will tell you the name of piece that it is using.

You can see Marc Maurer's Parallels project here:
https://objkt.com/collection/KT1TiSEcASGD19SW8bmqrqgSgCBkwXqDdTJ1

Obliques are also CC0, so feel free use anything here in other projects.

You can read more about CC0 here:
https://creativecommons.org/share-your-work/public-domain/cc0/

G : Toggle Grain
M : Toggle Matte
S : Save Image
1 -> 6 : Set pixel density
(Default pixel density is 1 @ 2000x2000)

metadata.name: Appropriate Hidden Breeze #506
metadata.description:
"Appropriate Hidden Breeze" is a study of blending gradients on a grid. 

Dependencies:
processing/p5.js
lodash/lodash
Jam3/nice-color-palettes

Export to a PNG format at several different sizes.
- Press s: save the current render size
- Press t: scale to screen size
- Press f: full print size 12x12" @ 300 DPI

metadata.name: FERAL #76
metadata.description:
FERAL tries to continue to explore further where PRIMAL left by adding more layers of noise to shape, distort and warp a grid to create topologies...

Enjoy and thanks a million times for being a part of my journey!
